After his diagnosis, he started his law firm. He was 1 of 8 attnys named to an Int'l list of innovative attorneys in the eLawyering movement, as a result of changes he made based on realities he experienced. He most recently worked for the Nat'l Organic Prog of the US Dept of Ag.

He received his undergrad degree from the Univ of FL & his law degree from the Univ of Chicago. He was an attorney w/Mayer Brown in Chicago, IL (practicing finance & securities law), & later worked for Goldman Sachs. He was diagnosed w/multiple sclerosis while at Goldman Sachs.

Student loans for which payments have been suspended are also treated as if the payments had been made for credit reporting purposes.

* unless such loans or obligations were already delinquent.  

#AskEllen  #EllenForIN2 3/3

Therefore, during the federal state of emergency for COVID-19, you should be able to enter into a payment plan or other accommodation with someone to whom you owe money without it affecting your credit.    2/3

The CARES Act modifies the FCRA to require lenders & other creditors to report as “current” any loans or other obligs. for which they agreed to any deferment/partial payment/forbearance/modification/assistance/relief until 120 days aftr fed. state of emergency ends (*) 1/3 https://t.co/kMsulOZJyy
